replies.body:
Some guy named whyrenekton (or something) left a comment on reddit saying kalista is coming, he/she is an adc which uses spears. (He also predicted yasuo, urf and gnar, now his account got deleted after leaving the comment about Kalista on reddit). OCE lol facebook (and no other league of legends facebook account) leaves a video showing a flag with 3 spears/ghosts. The 2nd icon, which you get from TT hexakill when you win 3 games, is the same flag but now with ghosts around it. On reddit i found this picture: QK8Vc0B.png. The last picture (The black/white one) was shown on some lol flags on a event. Also seven champions has been marked with the same mist as the flag video on OCE page: https://www.facebook.com/video.php?v=450651545076274. The seven champions: http://leagueoflegends.wikia.com/wiki/The_Black_Mist. Some say Kalista seeks revenge on these champions?
And on another event/same event this photograph was taken: https://fbcdn-sphotos-b-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-xap1/v/t1.0-9/10698469_623006454475062_6317513823333300794_n.jpg?oh=af8f6efa769bda412f0800da3a2a8243&oe=54E279C8&__gda__=1420763924_0709ae8559cbedac18bc23aaf10d021c
This is what we know so far.  Azir was released on aug 26, while ascension was released on 11 sep. And evertime riot releases a champ, it takes ages on the PBE to 'secure' champions for the live servers. If riot wanted to release a champ while TT hexakill is up, they gotta do it fast. Expect a champ in minimal 2 weeks. I got no lore story for you, try to read other peoples stories. 

